HEADWORD: Outburn
<hw>Out*burn"</hw>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To exceed in
burning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To burn entirely; to be consumed.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outburst</ent>⟦br⟧
